# ----------------------------------------------------------------------
# Windows-only artifacts MUST use CRLF, not the repo-default LF.
#
# Some Windows cmd.exe builds silently mis-parse LF-only .cmd/.bat
# files: every `set "VAR=..."` line is treated as an unknown command,
# `setlocal` becomes `'ocal'`, and `if not exist "%MARKER%"` always
# fires because `%MARKER%` was never bound. We hit this with
# installer\openclaw-launcher.cmd -- the launcher's marker check
# tripped even though the marker was on disk and visible to
# PowerShell's Test-Path.
#
# Inno Setup's compiler, the VBS host, and Windows' file association
# parsers all behave best with CRLF too, so we just make CRLF
# canonical for every Windows-side artifact in this repo.
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------
*.cmd  text eol=crlf
*.bat  text eol=crlf
*.ps1  text eol=crlf
*.vbs  text eol=crlf
*.iss  text eol=crlf
*.reg  text eol=crlf

# WSL/Linux artifacts must stay LF -- bash, systemd unit parser, and
# /etc/wsl.conf all reject CRLF (`bad interpreter: \r`, etc.).
installer/rootfs/**           text eol=lf
*.sh                          text eol=lf
*.service                     text eol=lf
